If you want to see if ANY difference in sliding window is >= z
Similar to sliding window maximum: https://leetcode.com/problems/sliding-window-maximum/
O(n) time O(k) space
```
        int count = 0;
        Deque<Integer> asc = new ArrayDeque<>();
        Deque<Integer> dsc = new ArrayDeque<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < k - 1; i++) {
            while (!asc.isEmpty() && nums[asc.peekLast()] > nums[i]) asc.pollLast();
            asc.addLast(i);
            while (!dsc.isEmpty() && nums[dsc.peekLast()] < nums[i]) dsc.pollLast();
            dsc.addLast(i);
        }
        for (int i = k - 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
            while (!asc.isEmpty() && nums[asc.peekLast()] > nums[i]) asc.pollLast();
            asc.addLast(i);
            while (!dsc.isEmpty() && nums[dsc.peekLast()] < nums[i]) dsc.pollLast();
            dsc.addLast(i);

            if (asc.peekFirst() <= i - k) asc.pollFirst();
            if (dsc.peekFirst() <= i - k) dsc.pollFirst();

            if (dsc.peekFirst() - asc.peekFirst() >= z) count++;
        }
        return count;
```

If you want to see if ALL differences in sliding window are >= z
Maintain a sliding window of size k (deque) containing int[]
int[0] = index int[1] = minimum value of abs(nums[index] - nums[j]) for j < index + k. 
Everytime we move forward one index, poll out an expired index from beginning and update k previous indexes with a new min. Find minimum difference and check if it's >= z.
```
    int count = 0;
    Deeque<int[]> diffs = new ArrayDeuque<>();
    for (int i = 0; i < k - 1; i++) {
        // compare in front of me
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int j = i + 1; j < k - 1; j++) {
            min = Math.min(min, Math.abs(nums[j] - nums[i]));
        }
        diffs.addLast(new int[]{i, min});
    }

    int count = 0;
    for (int i = k - 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
        int anyMin = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int j = 0; j < diffs.size(); j++) {
            int[] cur = diff.get(j);
            cur[1] = Math.min(cur[1], Math.abs(nums[cur[0]] - nums[i]));
            anyMin = Math.min(anyMin, cur[1]);
        }
        if (anyMin >= z) count++;

        diffs.pollFirst(); // remove expired index
        diffs.addLast(new int[]{i, anyMin});
    }
    return count;
```
